'''''Chrono Quest''''' ('''''Explora''''' in France)<ref name="Games Machine 1"/> is an [[adventure game]] released in September 1988 for the [[Amiga]] and [[Atari ST]]. It was developed by French developer Infomedia and published by 16/32 Diffusion in France and [[Psygnosis]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref name="Games Machine 1"/> ''Chrono Quest'' is an historical adventure where the player (accused of murdering their father) travels to different time periods on a quest to find their father's true murderer. The box art was designed by [[Roger Dean (artist)|Roger Dean]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/5839158/giant-plastic-alien-heads-badass-fantasy-art--video-games/|title=Giant Plastic Alien Heads, Badass Fantasy Art & Video Games|last=Plunkett|first=Luke|work=[[Kotaku]]|publisher=[[Gizmodo Media Group]]|date=September 12, 2011|accessdate=December 5, 2017}}</ref>

The game received mixed reviews from video game critics. A sequel to the game, ''Chrono Quest 2'', was released in 1989. ''Explora III: Sous le signe du serpent'' was never released in English, but saw a French release in 1990.  ''Chrono Quest 2'' had a similar critical reception.<ref>http://www.stformat.com/stf12/pages_nx1500/stf12_069.jpg {{Bare URL image|date=March 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kultboy.com/index.php?site=t&id=11527|title=Kultboy.com - DIE Kult-Seite über die alten Spiele-Magazine und Retro-Games!|website=www.kultboy.com|access-date=2017-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/ace-magazine-34|title=ACE Magazine Issue 34|date=July 1990}}</ref>
